@startuml fallback-tree
' A concrete fallback tree, its depth-first visit order, and where maxFallbackDepth cuts it.
' Source of truth: docs/src/resources/modelprovider.md
!include _style.puml

skinparam nodesep 24
skinparam ranksep 40

skinparam object<<attempted>> {
  BackgroundColor $gwBg
  BorderColor $gwLine
  FontColor $gwText
}
skinparam object<<cut>> {
  BackgroundColor $mutedBg
  BorderColor $mutedLine
  FontColor #555555
}

object "**anthropic-shared**" as p1 <<attempted>>
p1 : **visit 1**, the primary
p1 : type: anthropic
p1 : attempt slot 1 of 3

object "**anthropic-backup**" as p2 <<attempted>>
p2 : **visit 2**
p2 : type: anthropic
p2 : attempt slot 2 of 3

object "**anthropic-eu**" as p3 <<attempted>>
p3 : **visit 3**
p3 : type: anthropic
p3 : attempt slot 3 of 3, the last

object "**anthropic-apac**" as p4 <<cut>>
p4 : **visit 4**, never attempted
p4 : maxFallbackDepth reached

object "**anthropic-overflow**" as p5 <<cut>>
p5 : **visit 5**, never attempted
p5 : maxFallbackDepth reached
p5 : a child of the primary, yet cut
p5 : while the deeper anthropic-eu ran

p1 -[#1B5E20,bold]-> p2 : spec.fallback[0]
p2 -[#1B5E20,bold]-> p3 : spec.fallback[0]
p2 -[#9E9E9E,dashed]-> p4 : spec.fallback[1]
p1 -[#9E9E9E,dashed]-> p5 : spec.fallback[1]

note right of p1
  **A budget-blocked primary never falls back.**
  The gateway returns **429 budget_exhausted**
  immediately: the walk below never starts.
end note

note right of p2
  **A budget-blocked fallback behaves differently.**
  It is skipped, but its attempt slot **is** consumed
  and its own children are still walked. Contrast a
  statically ineligible candidate, which consumes no
  slot and whose children are not walked.
end note

legend bottom
  **The cut is across the visit order, not the tree levels.** maxFallbackDepth (default 3)
  bounds the total providers **attempted**, including the primary. Visits 1 to 3 take the
  three slots, so visits 4 and 5 are never reached, even though anthropic-overflow sits one
  level below the primary and anthropic-eu sits two.

  **Exhaustion never returns 429.** Every attempt failed at the connect layer: 503
  provider_unavailable. Every attempt timed out pre-stream: 504 provider_timeout. Anything
  else, including a walk exhausted purely by budget-blocked candidates: 502 provider_error.

  **Rule 11**: the tree must not be circular. **Rule 12**: every provider in it carries the
  primary's spec.type. The traversal algorithm itself lives in Fallback Logic.
endlegend
@enduml
